  "text": "A lot of work is being carried out to give better understanding on voltage stability, to detect it faster and to evolve a strategy to mitigate it once its likelihood is observed. To achieve this objective, it is essential to estimate the maximum permissible loading of the system using information about the current operation point. It means that the maximum loading of a system is not a fixed quantity but depends on various factors, such as network topology, availability of reactive power reserved and their locations etc. Determining the maximum permissible loading, within the voltage stability limit, has become a very important issue in power system operation and planning studies [CITATION_1] .",
